<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-839-262  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 839 262.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Sept 3 1990 v7 n36 p9(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>FCC to face massive budget, worker cuts. (Federal CommunicationsCommission)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Taff, Anita.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Federal Communications Commission (FCC) may have to reducespending by approximately 32 percent and lay off employees in FY1991 if Congress and President Bush do not reach an agreement byOct 1, 1990.andP;  Employees could be laid off for as long as 22 days,but not for more than four days during each pay period.andP;  The FCCis considering alternative ways of 'furloughing' employees,including alternating employees who are temporarily laid off sothat the FCC will not have to be closed at all.andP;  According to anFCC spokesperson, the budget reductions will adversely affect allFCC employees, as well as the FCC's ability to achieve its goalsin such areas as tariff filings and audit operations.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Federal Communications CommissionBudgetingCost ReductionWork Force ReductionNegotiationGovernment Agency.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraph.andO;Caption:   FCC budget history. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>